
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-keyring-3` yek barname ast baraye negahdari parol-ha va kalid-haye amniyati shoma dar yek jaye amne computer. In kar ra mikonad ta shoma niaz nabashid har dafe ke barname-ha ya web-site-ha parol shoma ra mikhand, an ra vared konid.  Mesle yek sandoghche parol mimanad baraye system shoma.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--start`  --> 🚀 Keyring ra shoru mikonad agar ghablan shoru nashode bashad.
    🔹 `--unlock` --> 🔓 Keyring ra baz mikonad agar ghafel bashad. Shoma bayad parol asli keyring ra vared konid.
    🔹 `--login`  --> 🔑 Keyring ra baraye session login fa'al mikonad.
    🔹 `--components` --> 🧩 Component haye mokhtalef keyring ra namayesh midahad (mesle ssh, pkcs11, secrets).
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Rahnamai dastoor ra neshon midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-keyring-3 --start --components
    
    🔹 Keyring ra shoru mikonad va list component haye fa'al ra neshon midahad.

    $ gnome-keyring-3 --unlock
    
    🔹 Az shoma khaste mishavad ke parol keyring ra vared konid ta baz shavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-keyring-3 --login
    
    🔹  Ba login be system, keyring khodkar baz mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-keyring-3` is a program that stores your passwords and security keys in a safe place on your computer. It allows you to avoid entering your passwords every time applications or websites request them. Think of it as a password vault for your system.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--start`  --> 🚀 Starts the keyring if it is not already running.
    🔹 `--unlock` --> 🔓 Unlocks the keyring if it is locked. You will need to enter the main keyring password.
    🔹 `--login`  --> 🔑 Activates the keyring for the login session.
    🔹 `--components` --> 🧩 Displays the different components of the keyring (e.g., ssh, pkcs11, secrets).
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Shows the command's help information.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-keyring-3 --start --components
    
    🔹 Starts the keyring and lists the active components.

    $ gnome-keyring-3 --unlock
    
    🔹 Prompts you to enter the keyring password to unlock it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-keyring-3 --login
    
    🔹 The keyring automatically unlocks when you log in to your system.
